<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch-5" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>The Laplace Transform and Applications</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      In the previous chapters, we  developed methods for solving initial value problems for ordinary differential equations with continuous forcing functions.
      In this chapter, we will extend our methods to solve initial value problems with discontinuous forcing functions and impulsive forcing functions modeled by the Dirac delta function.
    </p>
  </introduction>

